<h2>Programming Languages and Their Preferred Case Style</h2>

<p>Most languages have official style guides that mandate specific naming conventions:</p>

<ul>
  <li><strong>JavaScript/TypeScript:</strong> camelCase for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes</li>
  <li><strong>Python (PEP 8):</strong> snake_case for variables/functions, PascalCase for classes</li>
  <li><strong>Java:</strong> camelCase for variables/methods, PascalCase for classes</li>
  <li><strong>Go:</strong> camelCase for unexported, PascalCase for exported identifiers</li>
  <li><strong>Rust:</strong> snake_case for variables/functions, PascalCase for types</li>
  <li><strong>CSS:</strong> kebab-case for class names and custom properties</li>
  <li><strong>SQL:</strong> UPPER_SNAKE_CASE for keywords; snake_case for column names</li>
</ul>

